    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE COST OF SPRAYING</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Al Baker</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Baker, Al</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Larry Schwartz, chief adviser to Westchester County Exec Andrew Spano, says cost of mosquito eradication program in battling West Nile virus is expected to be about $1.5 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The cost of battling the West Nile virus in the county is expected to be about $1.5 million, Larry S. Schwartz, the chief adviser to County Executive Andrew J. Spano, said. The total includes $966,000 for both ground spraying to kill adult mosquitoes and the use of larvicide to prevent mosquito breeding. But more than $600,000 will be reimbursed through a state grant and other state aid, Mr. Schwartz said. The remaining costs were either budgeted or will be provided for through savings in other budget lines, he said, adding, ''Protecting people from getting West Nile is not going to negatively impact the budget.''</p>
        <p>Al Baker</p>
      </block>
